1
00:00:03,504 --> 00:00:08,306
<i>[ Broots ] JAROD SENT THESE.</i>
<i>FROM WHAT I CAN TELL, ALL TAKEN</i>
<i>WITHIN THE LAST FEW WEEKS.</i>

2
00:00:08,375 --> 00:00:11,643
THERE'S PORTLAND,
HOUSTON, LEXINGTON.

3
00:00:11,712 --> 00:00:15,147
SOMEONE'S
BEEN TRACKING US?
NOT US--

4
00:00:15,216 --> 00:00:18,016
YOU. LOOK.

5
00:00:19,386 --> 00:00:24,522
<i>FEELS LIKE THE HUNTER'S</i>
<i>BECOMING THE HUNTED.</i>

6
00:00:24,591 --> 00:00:27,759
<i>[ Ringing ]</i>

7
00:00:29,397 --> 00:00:31,730
- WHAT?
- SOMEONE HAS EYES FOR YOU.

8
00:00:31,799 --> 00:00:34,299
THE QUESTION IS, WHO?

9
00:00:34,367 --> 00:00:37,536
<i>[ Jarod ]</i>
<i>SOMETIMES THE ANSWER</i>
<i>IS THE QUESTION.</i>

10
00:00:37,605 --> 00:00:40,071
DON'T GET KWAI CHANG
ON ME, JAROD.

11
00:00:40,140 --> 00:00:43,441
OOH, I LOVE THAT GUY,
WANDERING THE EARTH,
HELPING PEOPLE.

12
00:00:43,510 --> 00:00:46,844
LIKE I'M TRYING TO HELP YOU
AND YOUR FATHER.

13
00:00:46,913 --> 00:00:48,847
MY FATHER? JAROD.

14
00:00:48,916 --> 00:00:51,650
[ Dial Tone ]

15
00:00:53,120 --> 00:00:56,922
<i> WHAT DID HE MEAN,</i>
<i> HELP YOUR FATHER?</i>
DAMN IT.

16
00:00:56,991 --> 00:00:58,991
<i> WHAT IS IT, PARKER?</i>

17
00:00:59,059 --> 00:01:00,992
<i>MY FATHER IS</i>
<i>STILL IN HIDING,</i>

18
00:01:01,061 --> 00:01:03,862
<i>BUT I RECEIVED A CRYPTIC E-MAIL</i>
<i>FROM HIM THIS MORNING.</i>

19
00:01:08,068 --> 00:01:11,002
DADDY TOLD ME
NOT TO TRUST ANYONE.

20
00:01:17,878 --> 00:01:20,512
THERE'S A CENTRE CONTRACT
OUT ON MY FATHER.

21
00:01:23,250 --> 00:01:26,017
WELL, THEN WHY-WHY
DID HE FOLLOW YOU?

22
00:01:28,822 --> 00:01:31,723
THEY PROBABLY THINK
I'LL EVENTUALLY LEAD THEM
TO THE REAL TARGET.

23
00:01:36,664 --> 00:01:39,097
[ Barking ]
<i>[ Chattering ]</i>

24
00:01:39,166 --> 00:01:41,499
DON'T ANYBODY TOUCH MY CARDS,
OR IT'LL GET UGLY!

25
00:01:41,568 --> 00:01:43,901
YEAH, HUH.

26
00:01:43,970 --> 00:01:45,903
AND HARRY CHEATS.
<i> YEAH, YEAH.</i>

27
00:01:45,972 --> 00:01:48,106
<i>[ Barking Continues ]</i>

28
00:01:49,143 --> 00:01:51,143
DAMN RACCOONS.

29
00:01:56,317 --> 00:01:58,249
<i>[ Footsteps Running ]</i>

30
00:01:58,319 --> 00:02:00,251
<i> [ Barking Continues ]</i>

31
00:02:06,694 --> 00:02:08,694
[ Growling ]

32
00:02:09,796 --> 00:02:11,629
<i> [ Mumbling ]</i>

33
00:02:11,698 --> 00:02:14,332
I GOT SOMETHING
FOR YOUR GARBAGE-EATIN'
LITTLE ASS.

34
00:02:19,473 --> 00:02:22,207
- [ Barking, Whining ]
- [ Screaming ]

35
00:02:22,276 --> 00:02:25,110
THE FISH IS SWIMMING
ALONG HAPPILY IN
ITS NATURAL ENVIRONMENT.

36
00:02:25,179 --> 00:02:28,913
YOU DROP THE HOOK IN,
YOU YANK IT OUT,
YOU CATCH HIM.

37
00:02:28,982 --> 00:02:32,183
-AND THEN AFTER ALL THAT,
YOU RELEASE HIM?
-IT'S REALLY NOT THAT CONFUSING.

38
00:02:32,252 --> 00:02:34,652
<i>[ Siren Wailing ]</i>
TELL THAT TO THE FISH.

39
00:02:38,491 --> 00:02:41,460
HEY, BOY.
WHAT'S GOING ON?

40
00:02:41,528 --> 00:02:43,628
HUNTERS CAUGHT SOMETHING FREAKY
UP IN THE MOUNTAINS.

41
00:02:46,200 --> 00:02:48,866
[ Chattering ]
<i> [ Screaming ]</i>

42
00:02:52,005 --> 00:02:53,872
[ Screaming Continues ]
[ Screams ]

43
00:02:53,940 --> 00:02:56,841
-<i> [ Man ]</i>
<i> IS THAT A BOY OR A GIRL?</i>
- [ Gasps ]

44
00:02:56,910 --> 00:02:59,711
- GET AWAY FROM THE WINDOW.
-<i> [ Man ]</i>
<i>  LOOK.</i>

45
00:03:00,781 --> 00:03:03,014
<i>WHAT KIND OF CREATURE</i>
<i>IS THAT ANYWAY?</i>

46
00:03:03,083 --> 00:03:05,850
[ Grunting ]
COME ON NOW. COME ON.
<i>[ Woman ] I THINK IT'S A GIRL.</i>

47
00:03:05,919 --> 00:03:09,220
DON'T MAKE IT ANY HARDER
THAN IT HAS TO BE.

48
00:03:09,289 --> 00:03:11,889
[ Groaning ]

49
00:03:11,958 --> 00:03:14,292
<i>[ Woman ]</i>
<i>OH, THAT POOR THING.</i>

50
00:03:15,996 --> 00:03:18,563
-<i> COME ON.</i>
<i> GET IN THE CAR.</i>
- [ Whimpering ]

51
00:03:18,632 --> 00:03:21,533
I'LL TAKE THAT.

52
00:03:24,704 --> 00:03:27,572
YOU EVER SEE ANYTHING
LIKE THAT BEFORE?

53
00:03:32,579 --> 00:03:34,479
[ Mumbling ]

54
00:03:34,548 --> 00:03:36,881
[ Screaming ]

55
00:03:39,052 --> 00:03:42,220
[ Siren Wailing ]

56
00:03:42,288 --> 00:03:45,424
<i>[ Man Narrating ]</i>
<i>THERE ARE PRETENDERS AMONG US.</i>

57
00:03:45,492 --> 00:03:47,425
<i>[ Jarod ]</i>
<i>I WAS TAKEN FROM MY FAMILY.</i>

58
00:03:47,494 --> 00:03:51,362
<i>THIRTY-SIX HOURS AND HE'S</i>
<i>ALREADY DEMONSTRATING MORE</i>
<i>TALENT THAN ANY OF OUR OTHERS.</i>

59
00:03:51,431 --> 00:03:54,533
<i>HOW MANY PEOPLE DIED</i>
<i>BECAUSE OF WHAT I THOUGHT UP?</i>

60
00:03:54,601 --> 00:03:58,035
SINCE I BROKE OUT,
I'VE SPENT EVERY MOMENT
SEARCHING FOR MY PAST.

61
00:03:58,104 --> 00:04:00,304
<i>[ Miss Parker ]</i>
<i>HE'S A PRETENDER--</i>

62
00:04:00,373 --> 00:04:03,675
<i>A GENIUS WHO CAN BECOME</i>
<i>ANYONE THAT HE WANTS TO BE.</i>

63
00:04:03,743 --> 00:04:05,944
- THE CENTRE WANTS HIM ALIVE.
- PREFERABLY.

64
00:04:06,012 --> 00:04:08,179
<i>[ Miss Parker ]</i>
<i>HE DEFENDS THE WEAK AND ABUSED.</i>

65
00:04:08,248 --> 00:04:10,014
LIFE'S A GIFT.

66
00:04:20,727 --> 00:04:23,528
-<i> YOU A DOCTOR?</i>
- I AM TODAY.

67
00:04:29,203 --> 00:04:32,437
[ Mumbling ]
<i> [ Man ] LOCATE DR. BENNETT</i>
<i> RIGHT AWAY.</i>

68
00:04:32,506 --> 00:04:35,039
<i> GET A LAB CREW, LINGUIST,</i>
<i> PEDIATRICIAN.</i>

69
00:04:35,108 --> 00:04:38,042
- I VOTE FOR A VETERINARIAN.
- THE STATE IS SENDING ONE
OF THEIR PEOPLE TO OBSERVE.

70
00:04:38,111 --> 00:04:40,278
<i> [ Man ]</i>
<i> A SOCIAL WORKER?</i>
<i> PSYCHIATRIST.</i>

71
00:04:40,347 --> 00:04:42,413
- WE DON'T HAVE MUCH TIME.
- [ Gasps ]

72
00:04:44,651 --> 00:04:46,985
- OH! DAMN IT!
- OH, STOP HER!

73
00:04:47,054 --> 00:04:49,988
GO! GO!
SOMEBODY STOP HER!

74
00:04:54,695 --> 00:04:56,995
[ Groans, Hits Ground ]

75
00:04:57,064 --> 00:04:59,998
<i> [ Man ]</i>
<i> IT'S LIKE SHE'S NEVER</i>
<i> SEEN A WINDOW BEFORE.</i>

76
00:05:07,841 --> 00:05:10,275
IT'S OKAY.

77
00:05:10,344 --> 00:05:12,343
EVERYTHING IS GOING TO BE OKAY.

78
00:05:19,586 --> 00:05:22,354
<i> IT'S OKAY. I'M NOT</i>
<i> GONNA HURT YOU, HONEY.</i>

79
00:05:22,422 --> 00:05:24,656
I'M JUST GONNA
CLEAN THIS UP.
[ Whimpers ]

80
00:05:24,725 --> 00:05:27,325
HOW YOU FEELING? HMM?

81
00:05:27,393 --> 00:05:29,961
<i> ALL RIGHT.</i>
<i> I'M ALMOST DONE.</i>

82
00:05:30,029 --> 00:05:33,931
YOU'RE MAKING A BIG MISTAKE
DEALING WITH HER LIKE THIS.
SHE'S AFRAID TO BE TOUCHED.

83
00:05:34,000 --> 00:05:37,168
WE'LL INSTRUCT OUR OWN STAFF,
IF YOU DON'T MIND, DOCTOR--

84
00:05:37,237 --> 00:05:39,337
BELL. JAROD BELL.

85
00:05:39,405 --> 00:05:43,141
THE STATE SHRINK FROM PROVO.
YOUR OFFICE CONTACTED US
ABOUT YOUR ARRIVAL.

86
00:05:43,209 --> 00:05:44,842
THIS IS DOCTOR BENNETT.
HOW DO YOU DO?

87
00:05:44,911 --> 00:05:46,945
HELLO.
I'M DR. WOLVERTON.

88
00:05:47,013 --> 00:05:52,016
I READ YOUR BOOK,<i> THE EFFECTS</i>
<i>OF ISOLATION AND DEPRIVATION</i>
<i>ON THE HUMAN PSYCHE.</i>

89
00:05:52,085 --> 00:05:55,520
YOUR THEORIES PROMPTED
A GREAT DEAL OF DEBATE WITHIN
THE PSYCHIATRIC COMMUNITY.

90
00:05:55,589 --> 00:05:59,123
MY WRITINGS ARE CONTROVERSIAL
BECAUSE THEY PUSH THE ENVELOPE
OF PSYCHOSOCIAL MEDICINE.

91
00:05:59,192 --> 00:06:01,459
WELL, IT'S ALWAYS DIFFICULT
TO BREAK FROM THE PACK.

92
00:06:03,196 --> 00:06:06,564
GIVEN HER PHYSICAL
APPEARANCE AND HER LACK
OF VERBAL SKILLS,

93
00:06:06,633 --> 00:06:09,400
SHE MUST HAVE BEEN ISOLATED
AT A VERY YOUNG AGE.

94
00:06:09,469 --> 00:06:13,738
THE QUESTION IS,
WHAT MADE HER SUDDENLY
DECIDE TO MAKE CONTACT.

95
00:06:15,475 --> 00:06:18,710
- EVERYTHING'S GONNA BE OKAY.
- [ Whimpers ]

96
00:06:18,779 --> 00:06:20,945
WE SHOW HER KINDNESS,
WE ESTABLISH SOME KIND
OF TRUST,

97
00:06:21,014 --> 00:06:23,281
AND SHE'LL BEGIN TO COMMUNICATE
IN HER OWN WAY.

98
00:06:23,350 --> 00:06:25,850
<i>WE DON'T HAVE THAT KIND OF TIME.</i>
<i>WITH NO LEGAL GUARDIAN,</i>

99
00:06:25,919 --> 00:06:29,020
WE LOSE HER TO SOCIAL SERVICES
IN 36 HOURS.

100
00:06:29,089 --> 00:06:31,422
YOU HAVEN'T BEEN ABLE
TO FIND ANY FAMILY?

101
00:06:31,491 --> 00:06:33,691
NO, THE POLICE ARE RUNNING
HER PICTURE ON THE NET.
UNTIL THEN,

102
00:06:33,760 --> 00:06:37,929
I SUGGEST WE TAKE ADVANTAGE
OF THE TIME WE HAVE LEFT WITH
OUR ONE-OF-A-KIND SPECIMEN.

103
00:06:39,933 --> 00:06:42,000
BRING HER OUT.

104
00:07:14,467 --> 00:07:16,901
WE WERE LOOKING FOR YOU.
GOOD NEWS, I HOPE.

105
00:07:16,970 --> 00:07:21,072
WELL-- [ Clears Throat ]
THE NUMBERS ON THESE PHOTOGRAPHS
ARE LEVEL ONE ENCRYPTION CODES,

106
00:07:21,141 --> 00:07:24,108
USED EXCLUSIVELY FOR
TRIUMVIRATE COMMUNIQUÉS.

107
00:07:24,177 --> 00:07:27,912
MUTUMBO?
THE ASSASSIN
UPLOADED THEM THROUGH
OUR SATELLITES TO AFRICA.

108
00:07:27,981 --> 00:07:31,749
I WAS ABLE TO ISOLATE
THE KILLER'S DESIGNATION.
HE CALLS HIMSELF "THE OWL."

109
00:07:31,818 --> 00:07:33,985
AND ACCORDING TO
PERSONNEL FILES,

110
00:07:34,054 --> 00:07:37,922
THAT DESIGNATION
IS USED BY MR. COX.

111
00:07:37,991 --> 00:07:40,058
THE GRIM REAPER.

112
00:07:41,794 --> 00:07:44,529
YOU CAN'T SAY JAROD
DIDN'T WARN US.

113
00:07:46,366 --> 00:07:51,302
[ Laughs ] BROOTS,
I WANNA KNOW EVERYTHING ABOUT
OUR PICTURE-TAKING FREAK.

114
00:07:51,371 --> 00:07:55,707
UH, MISS PARKER, I RAN
MR. COX THROUGH THE DATABASE.
HE CAME UP EMPTY.

115
00:07:55,776 --> 00:07:57,709
THE GUY IS
A BLANK SLATE.

116
00:07:57,778 --> 00:08:01,813
THE ONLY PROOF THAT WE HAVE
THAT HE EXISTS IS THE FACT
THAT WE'RE LOOKING AT HIM.

117
00:08:01,882 --> 00:08:05,483
SWEEP HIS OFFICE.
HE DOESN'T HAVE ONE.

118
00:08:05,552 --> 00:08:07,485
BUT GET THIS.

119
00:08:07,554 --> 00:08:10,121
I-I TALKED TO MY FRIEND RORY
IN PURCHASING.

120
00:08:10,190 --> 00:08:12,123
THE FELLOW WITH
THE ARTIFICIAL LEG?

121
00:08:12,192 --> 00:08:14,392
NO, THAT'S RUDY
IN PUBLIC INFORMATION.

122
00:08:14,461 --> 00:08:17,462
RORY'S THE ONE WITH THE
BIRTHMARK ON HIS HEAD SHAPED--
[ Stomps ]

123
00:08:17,531 --> 00:08:20,197
LIKE GUMBY.

124
00:08:20,266 --> 00:08:24,969
OKAY. ANYWAY, RORY TOLD ME THAT
MR. COX HAS BEEN MAIL ORDERING
SURGICAL SUPPLIES...

125
00:08:25,038 --> 00:08:27,472
AND HAVING THEM DELIVERED
AT THE CENTRE.
TRACK THE DELIVERIES.

126
00:08:27,540 --> 00:08:29,474
I'M ON IT.

127
00:08:36,717 --> 00:08:40,252
WHAT IF MR. COX REALLY
IS THE GRIM REAPER?

128
00:08:40,320 --> 00:08:44,322
ALL THE MORE REASON TO MAKE SURE
HE DOESN'T FIND MY FATHER.
HMM.

129
00:08:44,390 --> 00:08:47,392
[ Banging ]

130
00:08:53,266 --> 00:08:55,566
MAKE SURE TO KEEP
HER ROOM WARM.
YES, MA'AM.

131
00:08:55,635 --> 00:08:57,769
THANK YOU.

132
00:08:57,837 --> 00:09:00,671
I HATE TO SEE HER
KEPT IN THIS PLACE.

133
00:09:00,740 --> 00:09:03,841
I'M DR. SULVANE-- ANNE.

134
00:09:03,911 --> 00:09:07,044
DR. JAROD BELL.
I'M THE STATE PSYCH.

135
00:09:07,113 --> 00:09:11,149
<i>SHE NEEDS FAMILIAR SURROUNDINGS.</i>
<i>PLANTS, GRASS, SUNSHINE.</i>

136
00:09:11,218 --> 00:09:13,818
MM-HMM.
I'M SORRY. I'M AFRAID
THAT'S NOT POSSIBLE.

137
00:09:13,887 --> 00:09:16,154
WE HAVE TO KEEP
HER ENVIRONMENT STERILE.

138
00:09:16,223 --> 00:09:19,924
IF SHE'S BEEN ISOLATED HER
ENTIRE LIFE, WE DON'T KNOW WHAT
HER IMMUNE SYSTEM CAN HANDLE.

139
00:09:19,993 --> 00:09:24,596
WELL, HER VITAL SIGNS
ARE OFF THE CHART. B.P. IS
200 OVER 120, PULSE IS 150.

140
00:09:24,665 --> 00:09:27,031
- AT LEAST LET ME GIVE HER
A MILD SEDATIVE.
- NO MEDS.

141
00:09:27,100 --> 00:09:30,868
<i>AND I WANT MINIMAL INTERACTION.</i>
<i>WE'RE ONLY HERE TO OBSERVE.</i>

142
00:09:30,937 --> 00:09:33,871
HOW DO YOU EXPECT TO FIND OUT
WHO SHE IS IF YOU DON'T TRY
TO COMMUNICATE WITH HER?

143
00:09:33,940 --> 00:09:36,540
SHE'S UNABLE
TO COMMUNICATE, DOCTOR.

144
00:09:36,609 --> 00:09:40,778
AND THE HARD TRUTH IS,
SHE'S NOT GOING TO LEARN
FOR A VERY LONG TIME.

145
00:09:40,847 --> 00:09:42,780
I AGREE WITH DR. WOLVERTON.

146
00:09:42,849 --> 00:09:47,585
<i>WE HAVE A ONCE-IN-A-LIFETIME</i>
<i>OPPORTUNITY TO STUDY THE VERY</i>
<i>CORE OF THE HUMAN ANIMAL.</i>

147
00:09:47,654 --> 00:09:50,588
<i>SPECIMEN, ANIMAL.</i>
<i>HOW ABOUT HUMAN BEING?</i>

148
00:09:50,657 --> 00:09:53,090
<i>[ Banging Continues ]</i>

149
00:09:53,159 --> 00:09:55,727
<i>IF YOU'LL EXCUSE US,</i>

150
00:09:55,796 --> 00:09:57,862
WE'VE GOT TO GO MEET
WITH THE PRESS.

151
00:10:01,601 --> 00:10:04,102
<i>[ Phone Ringing ]</i>

152
00:10:04,170 --> 00:10:06,303
[ Sighs ]

153
00:10:07,340 --> 00:10:09,974
ARE YOU OKAY?
[ Sighs ]

154
00:10:11,444 --> 00:10:13,478
<i> [ Anne ]</i>
<i> I JUST CAN'T GET PAST</i>
<i> HER EYES--</i>

155
00:10:13,546 --> 00:10:16,948
<i> HOW SAD THEY LOOK,</i>
<i> HOW LOST.</i>

156
00:10:17,017 --> 00:10:20,585
YOU KNOW, IT ONLY TAKES
ONE PERSON TO MAKE A DIFFERENCE.

157
00:10:24,658 --> 00:10:27,424
CARDINAL RULE OF TRAUMATIZED
PATIENTS, DR. BELL:

158
00:10:27,493 --> 00:10:29,928
DO NOT INVEST EMOTIONALLY.

159
00:10:32,164 --> 00:10:34,566
HOW COME I DON'T THINK
YOU REALLY BELIEVE THAT?

160
00:10:34,634 --> 00:10:37,735
<i>[ Banging Continues ]</i>

161
00:10:50,383 --> 00:10:52,950
<i>WHERE DID YOU COME FROM,</i>
<i>LITTLE GIRL?</i>

162
00:10:55,321 --> 00:10:58,323
[ Chattering ]
DOCTOR! DOCTOR!

163
00:10:58,391 --> 00:11:01,359
IS THE LITTLE GIRL
ABLE TO SPEAK?
DOES SHE UNDERSTAND ANYTHING?

164
00:11:01,428 --> 00:11:03,361
HOW LONG HAS SHE BEEN
IN THE WILDERNESS?
FIRST OF ALL,

165
00:11:03,430 --> 00:11:05,363
WE DON'T HAVE ANY ANSWERS
AS OF YET.

166
00:11:05,431 --> 00:11:09,100
<i> BUT THIS IS THE FINEST</i>
<i> PRIVATE RESEARCH FACILITY</i>
<i> IN THE STATE.</i>

167
00:11:09,169 --> 00:11:12,470
AND WE'VE ASSEMBLED
A TEAM OF SPECIALISTS WHO ARE
THE BEST IN THEIR FIELDS.

168
00:11:12,539 --> 00:11:15,974
- WAS THERE ANY SIGN OF ABUSE?
- HOW IS SHE HOLDING UP
EMOTIONALLY?

169
00:11:16,042 --> 00:11:19,209
<i>[ Wolverton ] AS DR. BENNETT</i>
<i>SAID, WE HAVE AN EXPERT TEAM</i>
<i>WORKING ON THE SITUATION.</i>

170
00:11:19,278 --> 00:11:22,880
<i>NOW, WE'LL KEEP YOU UPDATED</i>
<i>AS THE SITUATION WARRANTS.</i>

171
00:11:22,949 --> 00:11:25,616
NO MORE QUESTIONS.
THANK YOU.
[ Chattering ]

172
00:11:28,388 --> 00:11:31,022
NO MORE QUESTIONS.
THANK YOU.

173
00:11:31,091 --> 00:11:33,825
<i>[ Chattering Continues ]</i>

174
00:11:33,893 --> 00:11:36,127
<i>[ Man ]</i>
<i>GIVE US THE ANSWER TO</i>
<i>A SIMPLE QUESTION, DOCTOR.</i>

175
00:11:54,314 --> 00:11:56,480
<i> SHE'S PRETTY.</i>

176
00:11:56,549 --> 00:11:59,717
- ARE YOU ON DR. BENNETT'S TEAM?
- NOT EXACTLY.

177
00:11:59,786 --> 00:12:02,253
DR. JAROD BELL.
LESLIE TWAIN.

178
00:12:02,322 --> 00:12:04,255
I'M WITH
THE<i> SALT LAKE CHRONICLE.</i>

179
00:12:04,324 --> 00:12:08,492
IF YOU COULD JUST LET ME GET
A COUPLE OF PICTURES, A BRIEF
INTERVIEW FOR MY PAPER,

180
00:12:08,561 --> 00:12:11,662
I MIGHT BE ABLE TO HELP YOU
FIGURE OUT WHO SHE IS.

181
00:12:11,731 --> 00:12:15,066
MY STORY WOULD BE SYNDICATED
ALL OVER THE COUNTRY AND--

182
00:12:15,135 --> 00:12:17,768
<i> DR. BELL IS NOT AT LIBERTY</i>
<i> TO GIVE INTERVIEWS.</i>

183
00:12:17,837 --> 00:12:20,271
REST ASSURED, EVERYTHING
IS UNDER CONTROL.

184
00:12:20,340 --> 00:12:22,373
<i> [ Glass Shatters ]</i>

185
00:12:22,442 --> 00:12:25,176
I'M SORRY, YOU'RE GONNA
HAVE TO GO JOIN THE OTHERS
RIGHT NOW.

186
00:12:25,244 --> 00:12:29,213
WHAT HAPPENED?
WHERE THE HELL
DID SHE GO? WHERE?

187
00:12:31,017 --> 00:12:33,050
DID YOU CHECK
THE MAIN BUILDING?
TOP TO BOTTOM.

188
00:12:33,119 --> 00:12:35,052
SHE HAS TO BE SOMEWHERE
ON THE GROUNDS.

189
00:12:35,121 --> 00:12:37,522
WHAT ABOUT THE PRESS?
WE MOVED THEM
IN THE COMMISSARY.

190
00:12:37,590 --> 00:12:40,558
WAIT A MINUTE. WHAT ARE YOU
PLANNING ON DOING WITH THAT?
IT'S FOR HER OWN SAFETY.

191
00:12:40,627 --> 00:12:42,760
THAT WEAPON WAS NOT MEANT
TO BE USED ON HUMANS.

192
00:12:42,829 --> 00:12:44,762
THE SUBJECT IS IN
A TOTAL STATE OF--
THE<i> SUBJECT...</i>

193
00:12:44,831 --> 00:12:46,831
IS A LITTLE GIRL WHO
IS SCARED OUT OF HER MIND.

194
00:12:46,900 --> 00:12:50,768
PLEASE, DOCTOR.
LET US DO OUR WORK.

195
00:12:50,837 --> 00:12:52,837
[ Chattering ]

196
00:12:52,905 --> 00:12:58,309
<i>[ Woman On P.A. ]</i>
<i>DR. WILSON, CALL EXTENSION 11.</i>
<i>DR. WILSON, EXTENSION 11.</i>

197
00:12:58,378 --> 00:13:00,378
WHAT NOW?

198
00:13:02,915 --> 00:13:05,916
WE FIND HER FIRST.
COME ON.

199
00:13:48,928 --> 00:13:52,163
- HERE WE GO.
TAKE MY COAT.
-<i> OKAY.</i>

200
00:14:20,727 --> 00:14:23,794
- [ Gasps, Whimpers ]
- IT'S OKAY.

201
00:14:23,864 --> 00:14:25,863
IT'S OKAY.
I'M NOT GOING TO HURT YOU.

202
00:14:31,270 --> 00:14:33,204
HERE.

203
00:14:33,273 --> 00:14:36,140
GO AHEAD.
TAKE HER.

204
00:14:36,209 --> 00:14:38,109
GO AHEAD.

205
00:14:45,384 --> 00:14:48,019
- [ Grunts ]
- [ Laughs ]

206
00:14:51,357 --> 00:14:53,290
YOU THINK THAT'S FUNNY?

207
00:14:53,359 --> 00:14:57,861
- I GUESS THAT IS PRETTY FUNNY.
[ Laughs ]
- [ Laughs ]

208
00:15:04,704 --> 00:15:06,704
[ Sighs ]

209
00:15:16,549 --> 00:15:20,485
SHE SEEMS TO BE REACTING TO
THE CHANGE IN HER ENVIRONMENT.
HMM.

210
00:15:20,553 --> 00:15:22,920
HER VITALS ARE STABLE.
SHE'S BREATHING EASIER.

211
00:15:24,090 --> 00:15:26,724
<i>SO WHAT DID YOU SAY TO HER</i>
<i>UP IN THAT TREE?</i>

212
00:15:26,792 --> 00:15:30,094
NOTHING.
WE JUST LAUGHED.

213
00:15:31,630 --> 00:15:34,031
<i> WHAT ARE THOSE PLANTS</i>
<i> DOING IN THERE?</i>

214
00:15:34,100 --> 00:15:36,600
THAT ROOM WAS
TO BE KEPT STERILE.
THEY CAN'T HARM HER.

215
00:15:36,669 --> 00:15:39,437
<i>[ Wolverton ]</i>
<i>THIS IS TOO MUCH INTERACTION.</i>
<i>THE SUBJECT IS TOO IMPORTANT.</i>

216
00:15:39,506 --> 00:15:42,407
THE SUBJECT? WHY DON'T
WE GIVE HER A NAME?

217
00:15:42,475 --> 00:15:44,976
ASSIGNING HER A NAME IS
ASSIGNING HER A PERSONALITY.

218
00:15:45,044 --> 00:15:47,044
IT COULD PREJUDICE THE RESULTS
OF THE CASE STUDY.

219
00:15:52,285 --> 00:15:54,218
VIOLET.

220
00:15:54,287 --> 00:15:56,688
VIOLET. I LIKE IT.

221
00:16:01,327 --> 00:16:04,895
- [ Babbles ]
- SHE SPOKE.

222
00:16:05,931 --> 00:16:10,601
<i>[ Babbling Continues ]</i>

223
00:16:12,539 --> 00:16:15,906
- WH-WHAT IS SHE SAYING?
- IT'S MIMICRY.
RANDOM PHONETICS.

224
00:16:15,975 --> 00:16:18,276
NO. SHE'S TRYING
TO TELL US SOMETHING.

225
00:16:20,546 --> 00:16:23,981
[ Babbling Continues ]

226
00:16:27,653 --> 00:16:29,653
-<i> [ Anne ]</i>
<i>  WHAT'S HAPPENING TO HER?</i>
- SHE'S GOING INTO SEIZURE.

227
00:16:31,057 --> 00:16:33,257
HELP ME HOLD HER DOWN.
[ Groaning ]

228
00:16:33,326 --> 00:16:35,259
<i>MY GOD, SHE'S BURNING UP.</i>

229
00:16:35,328 --> 00:16:38,296
DR. BENNETT,
I NEED MY MEDICAL BAG.

230
00:16:38,365 --> 00:16:40,297
<i>GET MY BAG NOW!</i>

231
00:16:40,366 --> 00:16:43,000
<i> [ Gasps ]</i>

232
00:16:53,113 --> 00:16:56,047
<i>[ Woman On P.A. ]</i>
<i>SOCIAL SERVICES,</i>
<i>PLEASE CALL 571.</i>

233
00:16:56,116 --> 00:16:59,250
<i>SOCIAL SERVICES,</i>
<i>PLEASE CALL 571.</i>

234
00:17:11,564 --> 00:17:15,032
HEY. YOU SHOULD GO HOME
AND GET SOME SLEEP.

235
00:17:15,101 --> 00:17:17,101
LATER.

236
00:17:18,304 --> 00:17:20,504
THE RESULTS OF THE TESTS
CAME BACK.

237
00:17:20,573 --> 00:17:25,110
IT WAS A COMMON FLU STRAIN.
IT WENT RIGHT THROUGH
HER DEFENSES.

238
00:17:25,178 --> 00:17:28,579
WELL, SHE RESPONDED
TO THE MEDICATION.

239
00:17:28,648 --> 00:17:30,848
<i>IT WAS SCARY TO SEE HER</i>
<i>SO HELPLESS.</i>

240
00:17:30,917 --> 00:17:33,918
ARE YOU INVESTING
EMOTIONALLY, DOCTOR?
[ Laughs ]

241
00:17:37,690 --> 00:17:42,026
I DON'T UNDERSTAND IT.
HER ROOM WAS STERILE,
THE PLANTS WERE INDIGENOUS,

242
00:17:42,095 --> 00:17:45,130
AND NONE OF US
EXHIBITED SYMPTOMS
OF BEING SICK.

243
00:17:45,198 --> 00:17:48,766
- I DON'T KNOW WHERE
THE VIRUS CAME FROM.
- [ Grunting ]

244
00:17:48,835 --> 00:17:52,070
OH, SHE WANTS HER DOLL.
IT'S THE ONLY THING
THAT CALMS HER.

245
00:18:05,351 --> 00:18:07,584
WHAT ARE YOU DOING?

246
00:18:11,458 --> 00:18:15,059
THIS IS A COCKTAIL
OF COLD AND FLU STRAINS.

247
00:18:15,127 --> 00:18:19,731
THERE MUST BE AT LEAST
10 SEPARATE VIRUSES HERE.

248
00:18:19,799 --> 00:18:22,099
OR 12.

249
00:18:22,168 --> 00:18:24,602
YOU THINK SOMEONE PURPOSELY
INFECTED THIS DOLL?

250
00:18:24,671 --> 00:18:27,271
UNLESS YOU BELIEVE THAT
A DOZEN INFECTIOUS VIRUSES...

251
00:18:27,340 --> 00:18:30,074
MAGICALLY INFESTED
THE SAME SQUARE INCH
OF MATERIAL.

252
00:18:30,142 --> 00:18:32,343
<i> WELL, I DON'T UNDERSTAND.</i>
<i> WHY?</i>

253
00:18:32,412 --> 00:18:37,816
SOMEONE CLOSE TO THE SITUATION
IS AFRAID THAT VIOLET IS
GOING TO BEGIN TO COMMUNICATE.

254
00:18:37,884 --> 00:18:40,919
<i> WHAT YOU'RE IMPLYING</i>
<i> IS CRAZY.</i>

255
00:18:40,987 --> 00:18:43,321
THESE MEN ARE THE TOP
IN THEIR FIELDS.

256
00:18:43,390 --> 00:18:45,323
WOLVERTON'S RESEARCH
HAS SAVED THOUSANDS,

257
00:18:45,392 --> 00:18:47,959
AND BENNETT'S WORK WITH P.O.W.'s
IN ISOLATION IS GROUNDBREAKING.

258
00:18:48,028 --> 00:18:50,661
I KNOW THE RECORD.
I DON'T KNOW THE MEN.

259
00:18:50,730 --> 00:18:52,964
WE HAVE TO GET THAT
LITTLE GIRL OUT OF HERE.

260
00:18:58,671 --> 00:19:00,605
I CAN'T BE A PART OF THIS.

261
00:19:00,673 --> 00:19:06,043
I SEE THE WAY YOU LOOK AT HER.
IT'S NOT JUST A DOCTOR-PATIENT
RELATIONSHIP.

262
00:19:08,214 --> 00:19:10,782
WHAT ARE YOU SO AFRAID OF,
ANNE?

263
00:19:16,155 --> 00:19:20,557
I HAD A SON-- MATTHEW.

264
00:19:20,627 --> 00:19:24,328
HE WAS A LITTLE YOUNGER
THAN VIOLET WHEN HE GOT SICK.

265
00:19:24,397 --> 00:19:28,966
<i>I TOOK HIM TO THE BEST CLINICS</i>
<i>IN THE COUNTRY,</i>

266
00:19:29,035 --> 00:19:31,702
THE BEST DOCTORS.

267
00:19:31,771 --> 00:19:35,639
- BUT I COULDN'T SAVE HIM.
- I'M SORRY.

268
00:19:36,976 --> 00:19:41,279
LOSING HIM NEARLY KILLED ME.

269
00:19:42,415 --> 00:19:44,548
I CANNOT GO THROUGH
THOSE FEELINGS AGAIN.

270
00:19:46,219 --> 00:19:48,219
NOT AGAIN.

271
00:19:50,556 --> 00:19:52,490
<i> [ Door Closes ]</i>

272
00:20:03,402 --> 00:20:06,871
<i>[ Bennett ]</i>
<i>DR. BELL. DR. BELL!</i>

273
00:20:10,009 --> 00:20:14,212
DR. BENNETT.
I UNDERSTAND THAT YOU'VE LOCATED
THE SOURCE OF THE ILLNESS.

274
00:20:14,281 --> 00:20:17,181
YES, AS MATTER OF FACT, I DID.
I WAS GOING TO SHOW IT
TO YOU IN THE MORNING.

275
00:20:17,249 --> 00:20:21,586
IT SEEMS THAT THE INFECTION
CAME FROM HER DOLL.

276
00:20:24,924 --> 00:20:27,057
THIS IS VERY DISTURBING.

277
00:20:27,126 --> 00:20:29,761
<i> [ Clattering ]</i>
WHAT WAS THAT?

278
00:20:29,829 --> 00:20:31,929
DR. BENNETT.
SHE'S NOT IN HER ROOM.

279
00:20:31,997 --> 00:20:34,198
WHAT?
THE LITTLE GIRL IS GONE.

280
00:20:34,267 --> 00:20:36,434
DAMN IT. DAMN IT!

281
00:20:43,909 --> 00:20:47,245
VIOLET. VIOLET,
WHERE ARE YOU?

282
00:20:51,651 --> 00:20:54,051
<i> [ Laughing ]</i>

283
00:20:57,690 --> 00:20:59,624
[ Laughing Continues ]

284
00:21:06,533 --> 00:21:11,168
[ Grunting ]
IT'S OKAY. IT'S MY CAR.
IT'S OKAY, HONEY. IT'S OKAY.

285
00:21:16,175 --> 00:21:18,175
YOU OKAY?

286
00:21:20,846 --> 00:21:22,780
WAIT, WAIT. STOP, STOP.

287
00:21:26,285 --> 00:21:28,986
I'D LIKE A SECOND CHANCE
TO HELP, IF YOU'LL LET ME.

288
00:21:42,334 --> 00:21:46,436
THIS IS THE FOURTH TIME COX
HAS PULLED OVER. WHAT THE HELL
IS HE LOOKING FOR?

289
00:21:46,505 --> 00:21:49,673
I NEVER PICTURED COX AS
THE PICKUP TRUCK KIND OF GUY.
[ Sighs ]

290
00:21:49,742 --> 00:21:52,109
<i>[ Miss Parker ]</i>
<i>YEAH, WELL, HE'S A BLANK SLATE,</i>
<i>REMEMBER?</i>

291
00:21:52,178 --> 00:21:54,812
<i>OH, WHICH REMINDS ME,</i>
<i>I TALKED TO RORY IN PURCHASING.</i>

292
00:21:54,881 --> 00:21:57,514
HE SAID HE DIDN'T KNOW
WHERE COX HAD THE SURGICAL
TOOLS DELIVERED.

293
00:21:57,583 --> 00:22:00,684
-<i> WE'RE GOING IN CIRCLES.</i>
- WAIT A MINUTE.

294
00:22:03,589 --> 00:22:06,557
-<i> WHAT'S HE DOING</i>
<i> WITH THE SHOVEL?</i>
- OH, CRIMINY.

295
00:22:06,626 --> 00:22:08,759
<i>THAT'S A DEAD SOMETHING.</i>

296
00:22:08,828 --> 00:22:11,962
<i>HE'S TAKING PICTURES</i>
<i>OF ROADKILL, JUST LIKE HE DID</i>
<i>WHEN HE WAS TRACKING YOU.</i>

297
00:22:12,031 --> 00:22:14,531
FLATTERING COMPARISON.
THANK YOU.

298
00:22:19,905 --> 00:22:22,706
TELL ME HE DIDN'T
JUST SCOOP THAT WORM BANQUET
INTO THE TRUCK.

299
00:22:22,775 --> 00:22:25,575
<i> EW. WHAT NOW?</i>

300
00:22:25,644 --> 00:22:29,713
STAY WITH HIM. IF THAT PSYCHO
GETS TO MY FATHER,
WE'RE ALL ROADKILL.

301
00:22:49,068 --> 00:22:51,335
WHAT MAKES YOU SO SURE
THAT THIS IS WHERE
SHE CAME FROM?

302
00:22:51,404 --> 00:22:53,504
THE WINTERS IN THE REGION
ARE FAR TOO BRUTAL...

303
00:22:53,573 --> 00:22:56,073
FOR ANYONE TO SURVIVE
WITHOUT SOME KIND
OF HEAT SOURCE.

304
00:22:56,142 --> 00:22:59,176
ACCORDING TO THIS MAP, THERE'S
JUST ONE HOT SPRING IN THE AREA.
<i>[ Airplane Passing Overhead ]</i>

305
00:23:02,449 --> 00:23:04,715
[ Babbles ]

306
00:23:07,854 --> 00:23:09,854
COME ON.

307
00:23:31,343 --> 00:23:34,712
THE WATER'S WARM.
HER HOME MUST BE CLOSE.

308
00:23:39,318 --> 00:23:42,220
[ Laughs ]

309
00:23:56,869 --> 00:23:58,869
[ Jingling ]

310
00:24:03,309 --> 00:24:05,242
HMM.

311
00:24:06,845 --> 00:24:10,147
INTERESTING.
WHERE DID SHE GET THE GLASS?

312
00:24:11,150 --> 00:24:13,984
OR THIS?

313
00:24:20,059 --> 00:24:22,026
<i>WHAT IS IT, JAROD?</i>

314
00:24:24,196 --> 00:24:26,597
I THINK IT MIGHT BE VIOLET
WITH HER PARENTS.

315
00:24:26,665 --> 00:24:29,367
<i>GOD. COULD IT BE POSSIBLE?</i>

316
00:24:31,170 --> 00:24:33,604
[ Babbles ]

317
00:24:33,673 --> 00:24:36,273
[ Babbling Continues ]

318
00:24:52,859 --> 00:24:55,526
WHERE IS SHE GOING NOW?

319
00:25:28,594 --> 00:25:31,595
[ Anne ]
OH, MY GOD.
IT'S A WRECKED PLANE.

320
00:25:44,743 --> 00:25:47,110
<i>JAROD, IT'S HER PARENTS.</i>

321
00:25:49,615 --> 00:25:51,682
DA.

322
00:25:51,750 --> 00:25:53,551
MA.

323
00:26:01,093 --> 00:26:04,095
DA, MA.

324
00:26:37,529 --> 00:26:40,698
- WHAT IS IT?
- LOOKS LIKE SOME KIND
OF VIDEO CABLE.

325
00:27:48,567 --> 00:27:51,735
<i>[ Clock Chiming ]</i>

326
00:27:51,804 --> 00:27:55,305
HOW'S SHE DOING?
RESTING.

327
00:27:55,374 --> 00:28:00,777
[ Sighs ] COULD SOMEONE
HAVE KNOWN ABOUT HER BEING
OUT THERE AND DONE NOTHING?

328
00:28:00,846 --> 00:28:05,482
YES. FROM THE LOOKS
OF THESE PHOTOS, IT'S BEEN
GOING ON FOR OVER 10 YEARS.

329
00:28:08,421 --> 00:28:11,221
THIS IS PERSONAL TO YOU,
ISN'T IT?

330
00:28:11,290 --> 00:28:14,158
YES. IT'S PERSONAL.

331
00:28:14,226 --> 00:28:16,494
YOU WANNA TALK ABOUT IT?

332
00:28:18,264 --> 00:28:20,264
YOU WOULDN'T BELIEVE ME
IF I TOLD YOU.

333
00:28:20,333 --> 00:28:23,133
TRY ME.

334
00:28:24,836 --> 00:28:28,505
- SOME OTHER TIME, MAYBE.
- OH, WHERE ARE YOU GOING?

335
00:28:30,042 --> 00:28:31,976
TO FIND OUT WHO DID THIS.

336
00:28:41,954 --> 00:28:44,521
DID SOMEONE DIE?
YES.

337
00:28:44,590 --> 00:28:47,024
WHERE HAVE YOU BEEN?

338
00:28:48,360 --> 00:28:50,894
<i>YOU REALLY WERE</i>
<i>AT A FUNERAL.</i>
<i> IN DOVER.</i>

339
00:28:50,963 --> 00:28:54,631
MR. COX, HE SPENT
THE NIGHT THERE. HE'S PRETTY
CHUMMY WITH THE OWNER.

340
00:28:54,700 --> 00:28:57,334
THE OLD GUY?
I'M RUNNING HIM DOWN,
BUT I DON'T THINK...

341
00:28:57,403 --> 00:28:59,569
HE HAS ANY CONNECTION
TO THE CENTRE.

342
00:28:59,638 --> 00:29:03,207
WEIRD THING THOUGH,
MR. COX ONLY CAME AND WENT
THROUGH THE BACK DOOR.

343
00:29:03,275 --> 00:29:05,976
WITH HEFTY BAGS.

344
00:29:06,979 --> 00:29:08,645
YEAH, I DON'T KNOW
WHAT'S IN THEM.

345
00:29:08,714 --> 00:29:11,047
WHAT COMES OUT THE BACK DOOR
OF A MORTUARY?

346
00:29:11,116 --> 00:29:13,917
BODY PARTS.

347
00:29:13,986 --> 00:29:18,422
WELL, WHATEVER WAS IN THEM,
HE HAD SENT TO
THE EAST WING OF SL 6.

348
00:29:18,491 --> 00:29:22,226
EAST WING.
THAT WAS THE INFIRMARY
WHEN I WAS A KID.

349
00:29:22,294 --> 00:29:24,227
I GOT MY TONSILS
TAKEN OUT THERE.

350
00:29:24,296 --> 00:29:26,597
WELL, I DON'T THINK
HE'S HANDING OUT LOLLIPOPS
TO LITTLE GIRLS.

351
00:29:26,666 --> 00:29:29,733
- NOT LIVE ONES, ANYWAY.
- EW.

352
00:29:31,237 --> 00:29:35,038
<i>I THINK IT'S TIME WE PAID</i>
<i>THE GRIM REAPER A VISIT.</i>

353
00:29:35,107 --> 00:29:37,408
[ Clears Throat ]

354
00:30:45,278 --> 00:30:47,211
GIVE ME THE PHOTOS.

355
00:30:47,280 --> 00:30:50,447
WHAT ARE WE DOING HERE?
I'M GONNA LEAVE THESE
FOR COX.

356
00:30:50,516 --> 00:30:53,083
LET HIM KNOW
HE'S BEING WATCHED TOO.

357
00:31:09,768 --> 00:31:11,768
[ Clinks ]

358
00:31:19,978 --> 00:31:22,046
DID YOU LOSE SOMETHING,
MR. BROOTS?

359
00:31:23,081 --> 00:31:26,817
[ Electricity Humming,
Crackling ]

360
00:31:31,690 --> 00:31:34,057
LOVE WHAT YOU'VE DONE
WITH THE PLACE.

361
00:31:35,260 --> 00:31:38,328
[ Sniffs ]
THAT'S RIGHT.

362
00:31:38,397 --> 00:31:42,065
YOU HAD YOUR TONSILS
REMOVED HERE, DIDN'T YOU?

363
00:31:42,134 --> 00:31:46,270
WELL, I HAD TO CLEAN OUT
THE OLD FILE CABINETS.

364
00:31:46,338 --> 00:31:48,338
OUT WITH THE FILES,
IN WITH THE BODY PARTS?

365
00:31:49,542 --> 00:31:51,475
<i>HANGIN' AT THE MORTUARY.</i>

366
00:31:51,543 --> 00:31:55,378
MYSTERIOUS BAGS
OF GOD KNOWS WHAT.
SCOOPING ROADKILL.

367
00:31:55,447 --> 00:31:58,882
- YOU FOLLOWED ME?
- YOU TAKE SURVEILLANCE PHOTOS
OF ME,

368
00:31:58,950 --> 00:32:03,253
<i> YOU BETTER BE PREPARED</i>
<i> FOR A LITTLE RETALIATION.</i>

369
00:32:03,322 --> 00:32:05,522
WHO'S THE GRAY HAIR?

370
00:32:06,658 --> 00:32:08,892
<i> HIS NAME IS CARL.</i>
<i> HE'S MY FATHER.</i>

371
00:32:10,062 --> 00:32:13,930
YOUR-YOUR FATHER'S
THE MORTICIAN?
MMM.

372
00:32:14,000 --> 00:32:18,235
WE USED TO HAVE LONG TALKS
ABOUT LIFE...

373
00:32:18,304 --> 00:32:20,904
WHILE HE WAS EMBALMING
THE CORPSES.

374
00:32:23,441 --> 00:32:27,777
NOW WE JUST EXCHANGE
TRICKS OF THE TRADE
FOR MY HOBBY.

375
00:32:27,846 --> 00:32:29,846
MY FATHER GAVE ME
AN ERECTOR SET ONCE.

376
00:32:29,915 --> 00:32:32,683
- HOBBY?
- MMM.

377
00:32:32,752 --> 00:32:36,286
TAXIDERMY.

378
00:32:36,355 --> 00:32:39,623
WELL, IT'S A SECOND CHANCE
AT LIFE AS A PART
OF MY COLLECTION.

379
00:32:42,294 --> 00:32:45,962
<i>THE EYES HAVE TO BE REPLACED</i>
<i>WITH GLASS ORBS.</i>

380
00:32:46,031 --> 00:32:49,065
<i> YOU KNOW, IN SOME CULTURES</i>
<i> I'M STEALING ITS ABILITY...</i>

381
00:32:49,134 --> 00:32:51,568
TO SEE ITS WAY
INTO THE AFTERLIFE.

382
00:32:53,839 --> 00:32:56,907
WELL, THAT'S DAD'S THEORY,
ANYWAY.

383
00:32:56,975 --> 00:33:00,109
DADDIES CAN BE SO MUCH FUN.

384
00:33:02,515 --> 00:33:04,448
SPEAKING OF WHICH.

385
00:33:06,985 --> 00:33:11,221
HOW IS YOUR FATHER
THESE DAYS?
WOULDN'T YOU LOVE TO KNOW?

386
00:33:15,160 --> 00:33:17,260
OH, MISS PARKER.

387
00:33:17,329 --> 00:33:21,064
THOSE PICTURES OF YOU--
I DIDN'T TAKE THEM.

388
00:33:21,133 --> 00:33:22,665
<i>[ Electricity Humming,</i>
<i>  Crackling ]</i>

389
00:33:22,734 --> 00:33:25,135
BUT...

390
00:33:25,203 --> 00:33:27,471
I WILL BE KEEPING
AN EYE ON YOU.

391
00:33:34,646 --> 00:33:37,648
THIS IS ONE FROM THE EARLIER
SURVEILLANCE TAPES.

392
00:33:37,716 --> 00:33:40,183
THE FOOTAGE WAS TAKEN
NEAR THE CRASH SITE.

393
00:33:56,401 --> 00:33:59,403
<i>THESE SHOTS WERE TAKEN</i>
<i>THREE YEARS LATER.</i>

394
00:34:06,211 --> 00:34:09,312
<i>[ Anne ]</i>
<i>I CAN'T BELIEVE SHE SURVIVED</i>
<i>ALL THOSE YEARS ALONE.</i>

395
00:34:09,381 --> 00:34:12,248
<i>[ Jarod ]</i>
<i>SHE WAS LIVING</i>
<i>ON PURE INSTINCT.</i>

396
00:34:20,425 --> 00:34:22,959
THIS WHERE SHE GOT THE WOUND
ON HER ANKLE.

397
00:34:25,897 --> 00:34:29,166
[ Screams ]

398
00:34:30,736 --> 00:34:32,669
THAT'S SOME KIND
OF ANIMAL TRAP.

399
00:34:32,738 --> 00:34:35,905
[ Screaming ]
<i> HOW LONG WAS SHE CAUGHT</i>
<i> IN THAT THING?</i>

400
00:34:35,974 --> 00:34:38,708
ACCORDING TO THE LOGBOOK,
THREE DAYS.

401
00:34:38,777 --> 00:34:42,579
- WHO COULD'VE DONE
SOMETHING LIKE THIS?
- WATCH.

402
00:34:52,358 --> 00:34:55,058
[ Screaming ]

403
00:34:55,127 --> 00:34:57,828
<i>[ Screaming Continues ]</i>

404
00:35:13,612 --> 00:35:16,579
<i> MY GOD,</i>
<i> IT'S DR. WOLVERTON.</i>

405
00:35:16,648 --> 00:35:20,050
<i>I'LL BE DAMNED.</i>
NO.

406
00:35:20,118 --> 00:35:22,219
BUT HE WILL BE.

407
00:35:27,960 --> 00:35:31,295
[ Elevator Bell Dings ]
WHAT DO YOU MEAN,
COX IS TELLING THE TRUTH?

408
00:35:31,363 --> 00:35:34,598
[ Clears Throat ]
I WAS DIGGING AROUND,
AND I FOUND THIS--

409
00:35:34,666 --> 00:35:36,600
LYLE'S EXPENSE ACCOUNT.

410
00:35:36,668 --> 00:35:39,902
THREE WEEKS AGO,
LYLE BOUGHT A VERY EXPENSIVE
LEICA CAMERA.

411
00:35:39,971 --> 00:35:43,473
WELL, WHAT KIND OF CAMERA
DO YOU THINK TOOK THOSE SHOTS?

412
00:35:43,542 --> 00:35:45,475
AND THEN THERE'S THIS.

413
00:35:45,544 --> 00:35:47,477
A CENTRE MEMO.

414
00:35:47,546 --> 00:35:52,382
LYLE NOT ONLY BROUGHT
MR. COX TO THE CENTRE,
BUT HE CREATED HIS POSITION.

415
00:35:55,888 --> 00:35:59,189
MY BROTHER IS BEHIND THE HIT.

416
00:35:59,258 --> 00:36:02,425
HE'S TRYING TO KILL DADDY?

417
00:36:02,494 --> 00:36:05,429
YOU HAVE LOST YOUR MIND.

418
00:36:05,497 --> 00:36:10,333
YOU TOOK THESE PHOTOS.
COX IS A CENTRE ASSASSIN,
AND HE WORKS FOR YOU.

419
00:36:10,402 --> 00:36:13,804
YOU'RE SUGGESTING THAT
I WOULD HAVE MY FATHER--
OUR FATHER-- KILLED?

420
00:36:13,872 --> 00:36:16,973
STOP TRYING TO MAKE YOURSELF
A PART OF THIS FAMILY.

421
00:36:17,041 --> 00:36:19,609
IF YOU LOOKED--
REALLY LOOKED--

422
00:36:19,678 --> 00:36:23,580
YOU WOULD SEE THAT
I'M JUST TRYING TO HELP HIM,
THE SAME WAY YOU ARE.

423
00:36:23,648 --> 00:36:26,850
YEAH, I GOT AN E-MAIL
FROM DAD TOO.

424
00:36:28,654 --> 00:36:30,654
SCARED THE HELL OUT OF ME.

425
00:36:30,722 --> 00:36:34,324
HE'S ON THE EDGE OF
SOMETHING TERRIFYING.

426
00:36:42,634 --> 00:36:46,436
HE TOLD ME TO TAKE
THE PHOTOS AND LEAK THEM
TO THE TRIUMVIRATE...

427
00:36:46,505 --> 00:36:49,372
<i>TO START ESTABLISHING A PATTERN</i>
<i>FOR YOUR ALIBI.</i>

428
00:36:50,976 --> 00:36:53,442
- ALIBI FOR WHAT?
- I DON'T KNOW.

429
00:36:53,511 --> 00:36:56,212
<i>HE SUGGESTED I START</i>
<i>A PAPER TRAIL FOR MYSELF TOO.</i>

430
00:36:59,083 --> 00:37:01,184
SOMETHING BIG
IS GOING DOWN.

431
00:37:01,252 --> 00:37:03,186
SO BIG, MUTUMBO'S
COMING TO TOWN.

432
00:37:03,254 --> 00:37:06,122
MUTUMBO'S COMING HERE?
ACCORDING TO DAD,
TO MEET WITH COX.

433
00:37:08,527 --> 00:37:11,995
I SHOULDN'T BE TELLING YOU THIS.
HE TOLD ME NOT TO TRUST ANYONE.

434
00:37:12,064 --> 00:37:14,297
HE TOLD ME THE SAME THING.

435
00:37:18,404 --> 00:37:21,171
SO WHAT DO WE DO NOW?

436
00:37:23,208 --> 00:37:26,309
WE WAIT, AND WE PRAY.

437
00:38:01,580 --> 00:38:05,081
<i>[ Bell Tolling ]</i>

438
00:38:18,930 --> 00:38:21,631
[ Shudders ]

439
00:38:22,701 --> 00:38:25,769
[ Grumbles ]
<i> DON'T BE AFRAID.</i>

440
00:38:25,838 --> 00:38:28,704
<i> HERE'S YOUR DOLL.</i>

441
00:38:31,910 --> 00:38:35,311
<i> I'VE BEEN WATCHING YOU</i>
<i> FOR A LONG TIME.</i>
<i> I WAS AN OBSERVER.</i>

442
00:38:35,380 --> 00:38:37,380
I NEVER INTERFERED.

443
00:38:39,150 --> 00:38:42,118
I NEVER HARMED YOU.

444
00:38:42,186 --> 00:38:44,120
GOD KNOWS THAT,
AND SO DO YOU.

445
00:38:44,189 --> 00:38:46,957
[ Mutters ]

446
00:38:47,026 --> 00:38:50,527
YOUR FATE WAS DETERMINED
BY THE LAWS OF NATURE,

447
00:38:50,595 --> 00:38:53,597
NOT MAN, NOT ME.

448
00:38:55,300 --> 00:38:57,934
HERE.

449
00:38:58,003 --> 00:39:02,439
<i>I'M SORRY I HAVE TO DO THIS,</i>
<i>BUT I CAN'T LET ANYBODY</i>
<i>FIND OUT.</i>

450
00:39:03,976 --> 00:39:06,409
[ Groaning ]

451
00:39:13,385 --> 00:39:16,419
SO WHO'S THE ANIMAL NOW,
DOCTOR?

452
00:39:27,099 --> 00:39:32,435
<i>[ Whistling ]</i>
HUH? OH. OH.

453
00:39:34,939 --> 00:39:36,939
WHAT THE--

454
00:39:39,244 --> 00:39:41,544
WHERE AM I?
WHAT'S GOING ON?

455
00:39:43,281 --> 00:39:45,648
<i>[ Jarod ]</i>
<i>DISORIENTING, ISN'T IT?</i>

456
00:39:45,717 --> 00:39:48,618
IMAGINE HOW IT MUST HAVE FELT
FOR A FOUR-YEAR-OLD LITTLE GIRL.

457
00:39:48,686 --> 00:39:51,121
GIVE ME MY CLOTHES.

458
00:39:51,190 --> 00:39:53,156
OW!
[ Groans ]
MY SHOES!

459
00:39:53,225 --> 00:39:56,726
I'D LIKE TO, BUT I WOULDN'T
WANNA CONTAMINATE THE INTEGRITY
OF MY CASE STUDY.

460
00:39:56,795 --> 00:40:00,029
BESIDES, VIOLET HAD NOTHING
WHEN YOU FOUND HER.

461
00:40:00,098 --> 00:40:03,133
IT WOULD'VE BEEN NO DIFFERENT
IF I HADN'T FOUND HER.

462
00:40:03,201 --> 00:40:05,635
I WAS JUST AN OBSERVER!

463
00:40:05,703 --> 00:40:07,637
IT WAS A SCIENTIFIC STUDY.

464
00:40:07,706 --> 00:40:10,340
OH, AND IT PAID OFF
FOR YOU, DIDN'T IT?

465
00:40:10,408 --> 00:40:15,078
BOOKS, RESEARCH GRANTS,
CELEBRITY STATUS.

466
00:40:15,147 --> 00:40:18,481
OH.
<i> ONLY YOUR DATA WASN'T BASED</i>
<i> ON SCIENTIFIC RESEARCH.</i>

467
00:40:18,550 --> 00:40:21,551
<i> IT WAS BASED ON THE TERROR</i>
<i> OF AN ORPHANED CHILD!</i>
[ Groans ]

468
00:40:21,619 --> 00:40:25,655
HOW LONG DID SHE STARVE
ALONE IN THE WILDERNESS
FOR YOUR STUDY, DOCTOR?

469
00:40:25,724 --> 00:40:27,690
HELP ME!
<i> NO CAN DO.</i>

470
00:40:27,759 --> 00:40:31,928
WHAT WITH THE COLD,
THE SLEEP DEPRIVATION,
THE HUNGER--

471
00:40:31,997 --> 00:40:35,431
<i>YOU'RE GONNA BE QUITE A SPECIMEN</i>
<i>WHEN THEY DRAG YOU OUT OF THERE.</i>

472
00:40:35,500 --> 00:40:39,069
OH, THIS IS CRAZY.
I COULD DIE DOWN HERE!

473
00:40:39,137 --> 00:40:41,538
YES, QUITE POSSIBLY,
YOU COULD.

474
00:40:41,607 --> 00:40:44,941
WE'LL JUST LEAVE THAT
UP TO THE LAWS OF NATURE.

475
00:40:45,009 --> 00:40:47,443
<i> UNLESS YOU CARE TO CONFESS.</i>

476
00:40:49,514 --> 00:40:53,115
<i> NO? OH, WELL.</i>
<i> HAVE FUN.</i>

477
00:40:55,186 --> 00:40:57,420
ALL RIGHT!
I LEFT HER OUT HERE!

478
00:40:58,590 --> 00:41:02,993
<i> I-- I LEFT HER OUT HERE.</i>
<i> [ Sobbing ]</i>

479
00:41:03,061 --> 00:41:06,729
GOD FORGIVE ME.
WHAT HAVE I DONE?

480
00:41:06,798 --> 00:41:08,865
[ Sobbing ]
<i> HEY, DOC.</i>

481
00:41:08,933 --> 00:41:13,469
WELL, HERE'S SOMETHING
TO KEEP YOU COMPANY
IF YOU GET LONELY.

482
00:41:16,608 --> 00:41:19,776
OH.
[ Sobbing Continues ]

483
00:41:40,666 --> 00:41:42,632
I DON'T KNOW HOW
TO THANK YOU, JAROD.

484
00:41:42,701 --> 00:41:45,001
I'M THE ONE THAT
SHOULD BE THANKING YOU.

485
00:41:45,070 --> 00:41:48,904
IT TOOK A LOT OF COURAGE TO SIGN
THOSE COURT PAPERS TO BECOME
VIOLET'S LEGAL GUARDIAN.

486
00:41:48,973 --> 00:41:51,273
I GUESS YOU COULD SAY
I GOT A MESSAGE.

487
00:41:51,342 --> 00:41:55,011
A MESSAGE?
AH, YOU WOULDN'T BELIEVE ME
IF I TOLD YOU.

488
00:41:55,080 --> 00:41:58,481
TRY ME.
[ Laughs ]

489
00:41:59,985 --> 00:42:02,652
I HAD A DREAM LAST NIGHT.

490
00:42:02,721 --> 00:42:07,323
MY SON CAME TO ME, AND HE SAID
IT WOULD BE ALL RIGHT.

491
00:42:07,392 --> 00:42:10,794
HE SAID HE DIDN'T WANT ME
TO BE ALONE ANYMORE.

492
00:42:10,862 --> 00:42:14,197
DOES THAT SOUND CRAZY?
IT SOUNDS PERFECT.

493
00:42:16,101 --> 00:42:18,101
[ Laughing ]

494
00:42:19,537 --> 00:42:21,704
IS THAT FOR ME?

495
00:42:24,710 --> 00:42:26,709
MMM. THANK YOU.

496
00:42:26,778 --> 00:42:30,179
AND I HAVE SOMETHING
FOR YOU TOO.

497
00:42:32,984 --> 00:42:36,152
[ Gasps, Sighs ]

498
00:42:49,234 --> 00:42:51,668
JAH-ROD.

499
00:43:03,815 --> 00:43:05,815
HAVE A BEAUTIFUL LIFE, OKAY?

500
00:43:15,493 --> 00:43:17,494
BYE.
BYE.

501
00:43:19,096 --> 00:43:22,431
YOU GOT A NEW DOLL.

502
00:43:22,500 --> 00:43:24,700
<i> [ Door Closes ]</i>
<i> [ Engine Starts ]</i>

503
00:43:24,770 --> 00:43:26,770
<i> [ Vehicle Departs ]</i>

